    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process of creating windows or other visual works using glass in cement or another matrix. Pieces of glass, usually slab glass, are laid out in a design or pattern; the pieces of glass may be cut, shaped, and chipped along the edges to resemble faceting. Cement or another material is poured between the pieces of glass, often with metal reinforcements, and allowed to harden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
